WEBVTT

00:02.378 --> 00:04.337
Hi, everyone. I'm Jeff Dunham.

00:04.338 --> 00:08.173
Greetings, infidels.
I am Achmed, the dead terrorist.

00:08.175 --> 00:09.759
I have a question for you, Achmed.

00:09.760 --> 00:12.470
I am all ears, without actual ears.

00:12.471 --> 00:13.930
All right.

00:13.931 --> 00:16.099
Who's your favorite
cartoon character?

00:16.100 --> 00:20.020
Is this a trick question?
No. Seriously, who is it?

00:20.021 --> 00:24.024
Tigger. As in Winnie the Pooh?

00:24.025 --> 00:27.193
Yes, and Eeyore. He was so sad.

00:27.194 --> 00:28.695
And Piglet?

00:28.696 --> 00:30.280
Don't be an idiot.

00:30.281 --> 00:31.448
Sorry.
Whatever.

00:31.449 --> 00:33.116
What is the point of this?

00:33.117 --> 00:35.368
What if you, Achmed, were animated?

00:35.369 --> 00:36.786
Me? A cartoon?

00:36.787 --> 00:38.747
Right.
Like Tigger?

00:38.748 --> 00:41.082
Sure.
That would be fantastic.

00:41.083 --> 00:42.417
Then wish for it.

00:42.418 --> 00:44.044
What?
Make a wish.

00:44.045 --> 00:46.755
Oh, like, "I wish I were animated"?

00:46.756 --> 00:48.089
Perfect.

00:48.090 --> 00:50.383
Hi, everybody.
Aah!

00:50.384 --> 00:52.552
I am Tinker Bubba.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.596
What the-
Hi, Tinker Bubba.

00:54.597 --> 00:57.557
Howdy. Did I hear
someone make a wish?

00:57.558 --> 00:58.850
Yep. That was Achmed.

00:58.851 --> 01:01.186
A wish? What wish?

01:01.187 --> 01:04.480
You said you wished
to be intoxicated.

01:04.482 --> 01:08.359
No, animated.
Oh, well, I can do that too.

01:08.360 --> 01:10.987
This is ridic-

01:10.988 --> 01:12.405
Ah! Oh!

01:12.406 --> 01:14.407
What happened to me?
Why do I look like this?

01:14.408 --> 01:16.659
Thank you, Tinker Bubba.
You're welcome.

01:16.660 --> 01:18.244
You infidel fairy.

01:18.245 --> 01:20.955
Toot-toot for now. Got to fly.

01:20.956 --> 01:22.766
Whoo-hoo!

01:24.251 --> 01:26.169
You tricked me.
You got your wish.

01:26.170 --> 01:27.837
And why am I like this?

01:27.838 --> 01:29.339
It's for your new animated special,

01:29.340 --> 01:31.049
Achmed Saves America.

01:31.050 --> 01:32.467
Enjoy the show.

01:32.468 --> 01:35.654
Come back, Tinker Bubba!

01:37.000 --> 01:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:57.034 --> 01:58.677
I will kill you.

02:01.789 --> 02:04.874
Oh, not a phone call
while I'm riding.

02:04.875 --> 02:07.585
I have coverage all
the way out here

02:07.586 --> 02:10.231
and not a cell tower in sight.

02:11.966 --> 02:14.050
Yes, yes.
What? What?

02:14.051 --> 02:17.137
Achmed. Why are you still alive?

02:17.138 --> 02:18.721
Nice talking to you too.

02:18.722 --> 02:21.599
Wheel of Fortune!

02:21.600 --> 02:24.394
I should have heard
a big boom by now.

02:24.395 --> 02:26.229
You have worked for
us for three years,

02:26.230 --> 02:28.940
and you still haven't
killed infidel one.

02:28.941 --> 02:31.526
I swear, you are the
worst terrorist

02:31.527 --> 02:33.236
in the whole non-Muslim world.

02:33.237 --> 02:34.696
I am not.

02:34.697 --> 02:37.198
As a devout non-Muslim,
I am offended by that.

02:37.199 --> 02:39.534
Are you forgetting you
blew up a training camp?

02:39.535 --> 02:42.412
The only thing left
was the monkey bars.

02:42.413 --> 02:46.875
Oh, please. We are so
much better than them.

02:46.876 --> 02:49.961
Do not worry, Hassan.
I will get it right this time.

02:49.962 --> 02:51.379
Achmed, focus!

02:51.380 --> 02:53.298
You're not losing
your nerve, are you?

02:53.299 --> 02:54.966
No!
Are you kidding?

02:54.967 --> 02:57.594
I'd be crazy not to
want to kill myself.

02:57.595 --> 03:00.013
Then tell me why you
are doing this mission.

03:00.014 --> 03:01.222
Because you told me to.

03:01.223 --> 03:02.599
Wrong answer!
Why?

03:02.600 --> 03:04.184
Because I hate the infidel.

03:04.185 --> 03:06.686
And why do you hate the infidel?

03:06.687 --> 03:08.438
Because you told me to.

03:08.439 --> 03:11.399
Right answer.
So don't screw this up.

03:11.400 --> 03:13.109
Why do you treat me like a fool?

03:13.110 --> 03:15.170
The bomb is ready to go.

03:16.405 --> 03:17.840
Oops.

03:24.288 --> 03:25.413
Huh?

03:25.414 --> 03:26.915
Hey.

03:26.916 --> 03:29.375
I'm alive.
I failed!

03:29.376 --> 03:31.127
Son of a female dog.

03:31.128 --> 03:35.173
Well, it obviously can't
get any worse than this.

03:35.174 --> 03:36.799
Huh!

03:36.800 --> 03:39.594
What the Hezbollah?
Let me go, you flying jackal.

03:39.595 --> 03:42.931
Release me at once.

03:42.932 --> 03:44.933
Clutch me again! I was kidding!

03:44.934 --> 03:46.827
I was kidding!

03:50.356 --> 03:53.233
Well, that used to hurt.

03:53.234 --> 03:56.712
Wait. Where is this
aluminum devil taking me?

03:58.530 --> 03:59.030
No!

04:40.572 --> 04:42.549
Mmm.

04:58.590 --> 05:00.008
Hmm. Hey.

05:00.009 --> 05:02.319
Death to America... ville.

05:08.142 --> 05:12.895
Terrorist log, hate date 7/3/13.

05:12.896 --> 05:16.316
I have arrived in the
land of the infidels.

05:16.317 --> 05:19.652
It will only be a matter
of time until-Aah!

05:19.653 --> 05:21.863
Oh, boy.

05:21.864 --> 05:25.074
I don't know what that was,
but it made a doozy of a noise.

05:25.075 --> 05:26.909
I hope we hit something cool.

05:26.910 --> 05:28.870
Then this day wouldn't
be a total loss.

05:28.871 --> 05:30.246
Whatever.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.081
Everyone's at the mall except me.

05:32.082 --> 05:35.001
And now my life is over.

05:35.002 --> 05:36.753
Well, I know we hit something,

05:36.754 --> 05:38.838
but darn if I know what it was.

05:38.839 --> 05:43.509
Turn around, asshat.

05:43.510 --> 05:44.969
Is that what we hit?

05:44.970 --> 05:46.346
Whoa! Is he dead?

05:46.347 --> 05:48.431
Can't we go now?

05:48.432 --> 05:50.641
No, honey. We have to help him.

05:50.642 --> 05:52.060
Here you go, buddy. You're fine.

05:52.061 --> 05:53.269
You're gonna be fine.
Wait. stop.

05:53.270 --> 05:54.771
Let me give you a hand with that.

05:54.772 --> 05:56.105
What are you doing?
Oh, that is a hand.

05:56.106 --> 05:57.440
Get your hands off of me.

05:57.441 --> 05:58.691
And the diaper goes on top, right?

05:58.692 --> 06:00.068
Wait a minute.
That's a knee.

06:00.069 --> 06:01.486
I don't even touch myself there.

06:01.487 --> 06:02.779
That's a...
What are you doing?

06:02.780 --> 06:07.158
...third knee.
Stop touching me!

06:07.159 --> 06:09.702
You put my ass in front!

06:09.703 --> 06:11.329
I'm sorry. I didn't see you.

06:11.330 --> 06:13.456
Oh, that makes me
feel so much better.

06:13.457 --> 06:15.416
I guess we should exchange
insurance information-

06:15.417 --> 06:18.127
Ooh.

06:18.128 --> 06:19.921
Oh, that looks like ours.

06:19.922 --> 06:21.589
Ew!
Oh,

06:21.590 --> 06:23.800
Can we get you to a
doctor or something?

06:23.801 --> 06:25.861
I want nothing to do with you.

06:29.348 --> 06:32.558
How I wish that evil airplane
had never carried me

06:32.559 --> 06:35.728
from my homeland to this
wretched America of yours.

06:35.729 --> 06:38.731
Mom, did you hear that?
He said he just flew here.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.233
Maybe he's our exchange student.

06:40.234 --> 06:41.818
Yeah.

06:41.819 --> 06:45.154
Claude, the French kid we
missed at the airport?

06:45.155 --> 06:47.448
I hate you, and I
hate this country.

06:47.449 --> 06:49.909
Oh, yeah, he's French.
We better stop him.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.869
Excuse me. Sorry to bother you.

06:51.870 --> 06:53.805
What? What? What?

06:55.499 --> 06:57.667
Ah! What devil is this?

06:57.668 --> 06:59.877
Bill, no.

06:59.878 --> 07:01.838
Bill? Seriously?

07:01.839 --> 07:03.714
You give your dogs people names?

07:03.715 --> 07:06.717
What did you name your kids,
Bubbles and Cujo?

07:06.718 --> 07:08.094
Billy, off!

07:08.095 --> 07:10.179
I'm sorry. He just likes you.

07:10.180 --> 07:13.099
Oh, great.
When does the humping start?

07:13.100 --> 07:15.601
By any chance, are you Claude?

07:15.602 --> 07:17.311
Of course I am Claude.

07:17.312 --> 07:19.105
I'm clawed, scratched, bitten,
licked, and humped,

07:19.106 --> 07:20.565
but mostly I am clawed.

07:20.566 --> 07:22.900
So you're saying you're Claude?

07:22.901 --> 07:25.486
Yes, you stupid American infidel.

07:25.487 --> 07:27.780
That's wonderful.
What?

07:27.781 --> 07:31.200
Claude, we are your
host family, the Wilsons,

07:31.201 --> 07:33.286
and we're so happy you're here.

07:33.287 --> 07:35.955
Are you infidels friendly or idiots

07:35.956 --> 07:37.874
or just friendly idiots?

07:37.875 --> 07:39.876
Sorry about the
mix-up at the airport,

07:39.877 --> 07:41.502
but that is all over now.

07:41.503 --> 07:43.171
Let's get you to your new home.

07:43.172 --> 07:45.173
You're taking me to your cave?

07:45.174 --> 07:48.301
Well, I do have a man cave.
It's the garage.

07:48.302 --> 07:50.219
Is he naked?

07:50.220 --> 07:52.472
Try not to make him
feel bad, okay, honey?

07:52.473 --> 07:54.015
He's probably poor.

07:54.016 --> 07:56.142
Let's get you a hot meal first.

07:56.143 --> 07:59.121
We have the foreigner.
Can we please go to the mall?

08:07.696 --> 08:09.197
I have moled myself,

08:09.198 --> 08:11.199
"first season of Homeland" style,

08:11.200 --> 08:13.576
among the enemy, the hated ones.

08:13.577 --> 08:18.181
These people who call themselves
Wilson are cunning, though.

08:20.167 --> 08:23.252
They insist on treating
me with respect

08:23.253 --> 08:26.464
and feeding me an
obscene amount of food

08:26.465 --> 08:28.275
that I can barely keep down.

08:34.640 --> 08:38.619
I have the same problem.

08:46.652 --> 08:49.153
Their town is in terrible shape,

08:49.154 --> 08:52.323
and their lives are filled
with emptiness and failure,

08:52.324 --> 08:54.033
yet they don't take
the obvious route

08:54.034 --> 08:56.744
of blowing themselves and
everyone around them up.

08:56.745 --> 08:58.204
What's up with that?

08:58.205 --> 09:00.081
I just work on the
assembly line now,

09:00.082 --> 09:04.168
but my dream is to design
the cars, like this.

09:04.169 --> 09:07.171
This is a gas-guzzling,
obnoxious testament

09:07.172 --> 09:10.508
to everything the rest of
the world hates about America.

09:10.509 --> 09:12.134
Exactly.

09:12.135 --> 09:14.345
It'll be a huge seller
and save the company.

09:14.346 --> 09:16.806
If only my boss would look at it.

09:16.807 --> 09:22.228
He will, because it's perfect,
honey, just like you.

09:22.229 --> 09:24.355
These are nothing
like the Americans

09:24.356 --> 09:28.568
I was taught to hate,
which makes me hate them more.

09:28.569 --> 09:31.571
Plus, I had no idea
women could drive.

09:31.572 --> 09:34.198
Well, this is your home
for the summer, Claude.

09:34.199 --> 09:36.409
It's cozy, but we love it.

09:36.410 --> 09:39.537
I am nauseated by the
evil stench of decadence.

09:39.538 --> 09:41.747
He did it.
Now, Kevin.

09:41.748 --> 09:43.457
Don't pick on our guest.

09:43.458 --> 09:44.834
He's had a long day.

09:44.835 --> 09:46.544
You know he was hit by a minivan.

09:46.545 --> 09:48.170
Why don't you and your
sister go toss the football

09:48.171 --> 09:50.256
or something?
Fine.

09:50.257 --> 09:51.882
I'm going to Angie's.

09:51.883 --> 09:53.718
Don't ignore your phone.

09:53.719 --> 09:56.137
It's not the phone I ignore.

09:56.138 --> 09:57.763
Kids today.

09:57.764 --> 10:00.266
In my land, they would have
both been stoned by now.

10:00.267 --> 10:01.934
That's right.

10:01.935 --> 10:04.270
You French kids start
drinking early, don't you?

10:04.271 --> 10:06.981
Wayne, remember our surprise.

10:06.982 --> 10:08.399
Oh, sure.

10:08.400 --> 10:09.835
Be right back.

10:12.279 --> 10:15.364
So now that I am deep in
the bowels of the enemy,

10:15.365 --> 10:18.534
I will make it my mission
to explode out a reeky,

10:18.535 --> 10:21.203
steaming vengeance,
but how and when?

10:21.204 --> 10:23.372
Ta-da!

10:23.373 --> 10:25.249
Are you Catholic?

10:25.250 --> 10:27.001
No, we're American.

10:27.002 --> 10:30.338
Claude, you got here just
in time for our town's

10:30.339 --> 10:33.633
100th birthday celebration,
and it's tomorrow!

10:33.634 --> 10:36.344
Ginny's in charge of the
parade and the fireworks.

10:36.345 --> 10:38.346
It's going to be some show.

10:38.347 --> 10:40.640
Fireworks? Explosions?

10:40.641 --> 10:43.726
Large crowds?

10:43.727 --> 10:45.269
We'll fix your room up, Claude.

10:45.270 --> 10:46.979
You go ahead.

10:46.980 --> 10:49.440
I'll just be here innocently
plotting and scheming.

10:49.441 --> 10:52.818
This is going to be
easier than I thought.

10:52.819 --> 10:55.196
Stupid Americans.

10:55.197 --> 10:58.091
They always leave their
dynamite just lying around.

11:02.037 --> 11:03.913
Let me go! I kill you!

11:03.914 --> 11:05.581
Oh, stop. Stop that.

11:05.582 --> 11:08.059
I cannot be murderous
when I am being tickled.

11:09.169 --> 11:10.544
I kill you!

11:10.545 --> 11:13.231
Stop it!

11:14.091 --> 11:16.801
♪ I've been working
on my big bomb ♪

11:16.802 --> 11:21.013
♪ All the dead long night ♪

11:21.014 --> 11:24.767
Dear diary, my bomb is complete.

11:24.768 --> 11:27.561
Tomorrow I will get my
revenge on these people

11:27.562 --> 11:29.313
who have been so nice to me.

11:29.314 --> 11:31.440
Here's a soft pillow.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.109
How I hate them.

11:33.110 --> 11:34.860
Is it hypoallergenic?

11:34.861 --> 11:36.696
Just like you asked.

11:36.697 --> 11:39.865
Yes, thank you, evil,
American, monster she-woman.

11:39.866 --> 11:43.494
You French have such
colorful words for everything.

11:43.495 --> 11:45.454
Oh, are you writing a book?

11:45.455 --> 11:48.791
Yes, it is a book of
humorous observations

11:48.792 --> 11:50.418
about small-town life,

11:50.419 --> 11:53.504
like the kind by your famous
instigator of suicide,

11:53.505 --> 11:55.005
Garrison Keillor.

11:55.006 --> 11:56.924
That's nice. Nighty-night now.

11:56.925 --> 11:59.218
Nighty-night.
Nighty-night.

11:59.219 --> 12:02.346
Hello, gorgeous.

12:02.347 --> 12:03.806
Hey! I want to talk to you.

12:03.807 --> 12:05.599
I don't have a bomb.

12:05.600 --> 12:07.601
You're not fooling me, kid.

12:07.602 --> 12:09.437
I know why you're here.

12:09.438 --> 12:11.605
Is that so?

12:11.606 --> 12:12.833
Well...

12:14.484 --> 12:17.236
My parents brought you here
just to make me look bad.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.321
La la la la.

12:19.322 --> 12:21.031
I can't compare to
how cool you are.

12:21.032 --> 12:23.367
You're from France and all.
I hate you.

12:23.368 --> 12:25.161
Aw, really?

12:25.162 --> 12:26.829
I hate you too.

12:26.830 --> 12:29.039
My dad thinks I should
be playing football,

12:29.040 --> 12:30.750
but I don't want to do that.

12:30.751 --> 12:32.460
I'm good at other stuff-

12:32.461 --> 12:35.463
secret stuff I've never
even told my parents about.

12:35.464 --> 12:38.048
You wish to lie with
another boy of your gender?

12:38.049 --> 12:41.886
No! I want to be a ventriloquist.

12:41.887 --> 12:43.429
A what?

12:43.430 --> 12:45.055
You know, a ventriloquist.

12:45.056 --> 12:47.099
I have a dummy. I make it talk.

12:47.100 --> 12:51.020
We tell jokes in front of big
audiences and get big laughs.

12:51.021 --> 12:53.105
That is a job?

12:53.106 --> 12:54.875
Yes!

12:56.526 --> 12:59.278
That is the stupidest
thing I've ever heard.

12:59.279 --> 13:03.199
Seriously, who is going to pay
to see anyone do that crap?

13:03.200 --> 13:04.950
But I'm good at it.

13:04.951 --> 13:07.203
I've been practicing
with my new dummy.

13:07.204 --> 13:08.496
Da-d a-d a-d a!

13:08.497 --> 13:09.789
Little Jeff.

13:09.790 --> 13:11.332
Hiya, Claude.

13:11.333 --> 13:14.919
That toy is possessed
with a human spirit!

13:14.920 --> 13:16.587
I pound your face with a shoe,

13:16.588 --> 13:18.088
which is the worst thing you can do

13:18.089 --> 13:20.007
to someone in my country
for some reason

13:20.008 --> 13:22.134
that no one has ever
explained to anyone.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.094
Hey, what's wrong with you?

13:24.095 --> 13:26.263
I'm sorry I said anything to you.

13:26.264 --> 13:29.141
This is gonna be a long summer.

13:29.142 --> 13:30.935
Or a short one.

13:30.936 --> 13:32.728
Aah!

13:32.729 --> 13:34.730
Whew.
It's only you.

13:34.731 --> 13:36.816
I thought you were
Jessica Chastain.

13:36.817 --> 13:38.317
Who's that?

13:38.318 --> 13:39.610
She was the crazy
bitch in The Help.

13:39.611 --> 13:40.945
What are you doing here?

13:40.946 --> 13:42.780
I was, like, out with my boyfriend,

13:42.781 --> 13:44.156
now my ex-boyfriend.

13:44.157 --> 13:46.784
Ugh. I hate him.
I wish he was dead.

13:46.785 --> 13:48.035
Hmm.

13:48.036 --> 13:50.454
Does he live within
a 20-mile radius

13:50.455 --> 13:52.164
of tomorrow's parade?

13:52.165 --> 13:53.916
Please don't tell Mom and Dad.

13:53.917 --> 13:56.877
The place where my lips
once were is sealed.

13:56.878 --> 13:58.671
They never liked him anyway.

13:58.672 --> 14:01.590
They think I have, like,
bad taste in guys?

14:01.591 --> 14:05.261
You? No.
Don't be so hard on your-

14:05.262 --> 14:08.389
Mwah.

14:08.390 --> 14:10.140
Wow.

14:10.141 --> 14:13.269
I felt something just now.

14:13.270 --> 14:16.564
Well, that was my detonator-
bomb, penis, nothing!

14:16.565 --> 14:18.774
You're so funny.

14:18.775 --> 14:20.067
Gracias?

14:20.068 --> 14:22.403
And I love your French accent.

14:22.404 --> 14:24.196
Cassidy, are you home?

14:24.197 --> 14:27.074
Got to go.
I'll love you till I die.

14:27.075 --> 14:31.262
Stay within the 20-mile radius.

14:32.664 --> 14:35.416
Good night, Cassidy.
Good night, Mom.

14:35.417 --> 14:38.002
Good night, Kevin.
Good night, Dad!

14:38.003 --> 14:39.587
Good night, Ginny!

14:39.588 --> 14:41.005
Why are you screaming at me

14:41.006 --> 14:42.590
when I'm lying right next to you?

14:42.591 --> 14:43.716
Sorry, honey!

14:43.717 --> 14:44.842
Good night, little Jeff!

14:44.843 --> 14:45.968
Good night, "ethery-diddy"!

14:45.969 --> 14:47.177
Silence!

14:47.178 --> 14:50.824
Good night, bomb.

15:00.734 --> 15:03.152
Great job, Mom.

15:03.153 --> 15:05.571
Thanks.
And don't you two look nice.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.281
Yeah, I got this shirt at the-

15:07.282 --> 15:08.908
Ah! It's almost time
for the show to start.

15:08.909 --> 15:10.534
Kevin, do you know where Claude is?

15:10.535 --> 15:12.536
No, Mom, I don't.

15:12.537 --> 15:15.205
"Claude. Claude. Where's Claude?"

15:15.206 --> 15:17.041
Everybody loves the French guy.

15:17.042 --> 15:18.500
He was in the car with us.

